@startuml
' VibeTags Build Sequence Diagram

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam sequence {
    ArrowColor #1565C0
    ActorBorderColor #1565C0
    LifeLineBorderColor #2196F3
    ParticipantBorderColor #2196F3
}

title VibeTags Build Sequence - Annotation Processing Flow

actor Developer
participant "javac\nCompiler" as Compiler
participant "AIGuardrailProcessor" as Processor
participant "VibeTagsLogger" as Logger
participant "File System" as FS
participant "AI Platform\nConfig Files" as AIFiles

== Build Initiation ==
Developer -> Compiler: mvn clean compile
activate Compiler
Compiler -> Compiler: Parse pom.xml\nResolve dependencies

== Processor Initialisation ==
Compiler -> Compiler: Discover AIGuardrailProcessor\nvia META-INF/services
note right: SPI registration

Compiler -> Processor: init(processingEnv)
activate Processor
Processor -> Processor: Resolve root directory\n(vibetags.root option or JVM cwd)
Processor -> Logger: forRoot(root, logPath, logLevel)
Processor -> Processor: Reset element sets\nand initialise StringBuilders

== Processing Rounds (may be multiple) ==
loop Each compilation round
    Compiler -> Processor: process(annotations, roundEnv)

    alt processingOver() == true AND not yet processed
        Processor -> Processor: generateFiles()
        note right: See "File Generation" section below
        Processor -> Processor: Set processed = true
        Processor --> Compiler: return false
    else processingOver() == true AND already processed
        Processor --> Compiler: return false (idempotency guard)
    else Normal round — accumulate elements
        Processor -> Processor: Accumulate @AILocked elements
        Processor -> Processor: Accumulate @AIContext elements
        Processor -> Processor: Accumulate @AIIgnore elements
        Processor -> Processor: Accumulate @AIAudit elements
        Processor -> Processor: Accumulate @AIDraft elements
        Processor -> Processor: Accumulate @AIPrivacy elements
        Processor -> Processor: Accumulate @AICore elements
        Processor -> Processor: Accumulate @AIPerformance elements

        == Validation Phase (each round) ==
        Processor -> Processor: validateAnnotations()
        note right
            Checks:
            - @AIDraft + @AILocked contradiction
            - Empty @AIAudit checkFor array
            - @AIPrivacy + @AIIgnore redundancy
        end note
        Processor --> Compiler: return false
    end
end

== File Generation (triggered on final round) ==
Processor -> Processor: buildServiceFileMap(root)
Processor -> FS: Files.exists() for each signal file
FS --> Processor: Active service keys

note over Processor
  Content generation — per annotation type, per platform:
  @AILocked  → locked_files / LOCKED FILES section
  @AIContext → contextual_instructions / CONTEXTUAL RULES
  @AIIgnore  → ignored_elements + glob patterns
  @AIAudit   → audit_requirements / SECURITY AUDITS
  @AIDraft   → implementation_tasks / TASKS
  @AIPrivacy → pii_guardrails / PII GUARDRAILS
  @AICore    → core_elements / CORE FUNCTIONALITY
  @AIPerf    → performance_constraints / PERF CONSTRAINTS
end note

loop For each active service
    alt Marker-based file (.md, rules, txt)
        Processor -> FS: Read existing content
        Processor -> Processor: Update VIBETAGS-START…END section\nPreserve human content outside markers
    else JSON / TOML
        Processor -> Processor: Complete overwrite
    end

    alt Content changed AND hasNewRules
        Processor -> FS: writeContentWithBackup(filePath, content)
        FS -> AIFiles: Write updated file
        Processor -> Compiler: NOTE: "updated - <file>"
        Processor -> Logger: info("{} — updated", relPath)
    else hasNewRules == false AND non-empty file
        Processor -> Compiler: NOTE: "Skipping update — multi-module"
    else Content unchanged
        Processor -> Compiler: NOTE: "no changes - <file>"
    end
end

loop Per annotated class (granular rules)
    Processor -> FS: Write .cursor/rules/<Class>.mdc
    Processor -> FS: Write .trae/rules/<Class>.md
    Processor -> FS: Write .roo/rules/<Class>.md
end

Processor -> FS: cleanupGranularDirectory()\nRemove orphaned rule files

== Post-Generation ==
Processor -> Processor: checkOrphanedAnnotations()
note right
    Warns if annotations used
    but recommended files missing.
    E.g.: @AIIgnore without .qwenignore
end note

deactivate Processor
Compiler --> Developer: BUILD SUCCESS
deactivate Compiler

== Developer Uses AI Tools ==
Developer -> AIFiles: AI tool reads CLAUDE.md, llms.txt, etc.
note right
    AI platforms read generated config files
    to enforce guardrails during coding sessions.
    llms.txt is the entry point for LLM agents.
end note

@enduml
